    "Gradient boosting clinches the second spot in recall and F1 score for bearish predictions, whereas the decision tree model does so for bullish forecasts.",
    "In stark contrast, the naive Bayes model trails behind, consistently recording the least recall and F1 score for both bearish and bullish predictions.",
    "In essence, the graphical analysis emphasizes the random forest model's exceptional ability to predict Microsoft stock price trends, setting it apart as the most adept performer among the evaluated models.Table 3 Comparison of Model Performances for Google StockIn Table 3, identifying Google Stock Bearish trends, Random Forest exhibited the highest accuracy at 96%, followed by Gradient Boosting (98%) and Extra Trees (90%).",
    "In terms of recall, Random Forest achieved perfect recall (100%), outperforming all other models, while Gradient Boosting and Extra Trees scored 91% and 77%, respectively.",
    "Conversely, in identifying Bullish trends, Random Forest again emerged with the highest accuracy of 100%, followed by Decision Tree (89%) and Gradient Boosting (93%)."
